<br>
Claws of Veeshan<br>
Othmir<br>
Sirens/Sirens Grotto<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Are the drakes and the main dragon of the zone on templeveeshan faction?</i><br>
<br>
Kelorek Dar is on Claws of Veeshan faction, yes. Cobalt drakes have none.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Will quad kiting wyverns lower this faction?</i><br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Do I have to worry about the drakes' AoE spell?</i><br>
<br>
Yes, if other players are hunting them near you, you might get hit. Stay clear of those groups. Otherwise if you just root/dot one at a good distance, there is nothing to fear from its AE. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Any basic tips on this zone would help me out a lot.</i> <br>
<br>
Having good Claws of Veeshan faction helps hunting in this zone A LOT. Egress takes you to the beach by an Othmir camp. Use it if you're not KOS to otters (obviously). If you don't have Egress and you are KOS to wyverns and drakes, bind at the SG zone entrance, then gate and zone to clear aggro. If you are not KOS to wyverns, you can bind in the tower (Skyshrine zone entrance). <br>
<br>
Don't quadkite if the zone is full; it really gives druids such a good reputation. <br>
<br>
To pull a wyvern near Yvolcarn, use Harmony on Yvolcarn. As for Azureake, avoid kiting a wyvern/drake or rotting one in its flight path -- obviously.  <p><center>Gwynhyfar Foxfyre<br>
